<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>7834</id>
	<title>user logged into facebook is not logged into canvas application on IE</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Hi_</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">This is an issue which occurs on IE and Safari_ it does not occur on Firefox.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">If you login to facebook as normal and then browse to the apps page_ the application which is sitting embedded in the canvas is not passed the logged in status and hence is not authenticated.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Here are the steps to reproduce.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.1">1 Browse to http://www.facebook.com and login with your username and password.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.1">2 Browse to http://apps.facebook.com/christmas_carol_test/</sentence>
			<sentence id="6.1">3 Select a language_ say_ English and click  Continue</sentence>
			<sentence id="7.1">4 You will see a message which says  authenticated: False .</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="8">
			<sentence id="8.1">If you repeat the steps above on Firefox_ it appears as authenticated: True.</sentence>
			<sentence id="8.2">It seems like IE and Safari are not allowing the authentication to take place in the iframe.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="9">
			<sentence id="9.1">Is there a solution / work around for this?</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="10">
			<sentence id="10.1">Thank You_</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="11">
			<sentence id="11.1">Keith.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
